When more than 1 calendars are being viewed on same calendar macro, zooming in make events to appear overlapped on same time row. This makes impossible to distinguish start and end dates of events when multiple calendars are being viewed.

Steps to replicate:
1) Create new calendar A;
2) Insert two new events on calendar A;
3) Create new calendar B;
2) Insert two new events on calendar B, with same start and end dates of those ones created on step 2;
3) Go to "My Calendars" view and zoom in.
4) Check that the events go down to the same time row, and now it's impossible to distinguish them.

This also can be seen on Team Calendar macro.

